          <h1 class="heading-black text-capitalize">Grain Storage Technology.</h1>
          <p class="lead py-3">Grain storage technology aims to preserve the quality and quantity of harvested grain by controlling moisture, temperature, pests, and external factors. The objectives of this technology are to ensure food security, economic returns for farmers, and sustained supply for consumers. By adopting appropriate storage methods and techniques, losses due to spoilage or wastage can be reduced, while efficient use of storage space can be maximized. Ultimately, the goal is to provide safe, affordable, and accessible storage solutions for all stakeholders in the food value chain.
          </p>
