          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
              <h6>What is grain storage technology?</h6>
              <p class="text-muted">Grain storage technology refers to the techniques and methods used to store harvested grains to maintain their quality and prevent spoilage</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
              <h6>Why is grain storage important?</h6>
              <p class="text-muted">Grain storage is important to preserve the quality and quantity of harvested grains until they can be sold or used. Proper storage techniques help prevent spoilage, insect and rodent infestations, and moisture damage</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
              <h6>How long can grains be stored?</h6>
              <p class="text-muted">The length of time grains can be stored depends on the type of grain, storage conditions, and other factors. Some grains can be stored for several years under proper conditions, while others have a shorter storage life</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
              <h6>How often do you release updates?</h6>
              <p class="text-muted">We release updates once in two months</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
              <h6>What are some signs of spoilage in stored grains?</h6>
              <p class="text-muted">Signs of spoilage in stored grains include mold growth, off odors, discoloration, insect or rodent infestations, and changes in texture or appearance.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
